<br>
You are one of the funnest KEI'ers on PoK...please don't stop.<br>
<br>
I really also enjoyed the illusion you cast on the other day as well (scarecrow) Unfortunately I went LD shortly after that and lost it...I was so looking forward to surprising my guildies later that evening at our guild gathering.<!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :rollin --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/roll.gif ALT=":rollin"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END--> <br>
<br>
I am a wizardress that enjoys having KEI cast on me.  As you might know most of our nukes can be quite mana intensive and having KEI often helps.  Now that I've got my INT almost max'd tho I find it not so necessary and will often hunt without that aid.<br>
<br>
All the KEI casters have been most gracious to me...often casting for free even without my hailing them (I cannot remember the last time I sent a /tell to anyone asking for kei).  If I'm interested in getting a KEI i ask on the /kei channel and go to where it's advertised that it's available.  I have no problem making a donation for the gift of KEI and try to be generous as I able in my donation.  I ALWAYS thank the caster (no excuse for rudeness I always say) even if i do make a donation.  They have made themselves and their talent available, regardless of what their motivation, and i appreciate that.<br>
<br>
As far as casting for donations...I too am guilty of porting for donations.  Spells cost plat and so does any worthwhile item in bazaar (seen the prices lately...now that a crime!)  I also sell pies and truffles I have produced through my baking skills on PoK, in Bazaar, and on the /market channel.<br>
<br>
I often TL for free whenever approached and never accept anything for someone trying to get back to their corpse <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :x --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/sick.gif ALT=":x"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END-->   I have accepted donations anywhere from 2pp to 100pp for a single port and I'm not ashamed to do that...portal shards don't grow on trees (tho aren't really expensive) and I never seem to make back my pp investment in my baking (i give alot of pies away <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :lol --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/laugh.gif ALT=":lol"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END--> ).<br>
<br>
Just my 2cp worth.<br>
