<br>
If I see shout after shout of people looking for KEI with no response from someone who actually <!--EZCODE BOLD START--><strong>wants</strong><!--EZCODE BOLD END--> to provide that service, I will very rarely cast it on people out of the limited kindness of my small heart. I don't ask for anything, but hit accept trade on whatever is thrust at me.<br>
<br>
But I had a very annoying episode a few days ago. I was just standing near the Nexus stone, cause I had stopped to chat with someone. I was accidentally not in Role mode. Someone just walked up behind me, and handed me 40pp.<br>
<br>
This irritated me, so I hit accept trade, and continued my conversation, just to see what the person would do.<br>
<br>
Still standing behind me, I get a tell a few minutes later saying &quot;dude, WTF!!!! you gonna cast KEI or not????&quot;.<br>
<br>
I slowly turned to face them, and said &quot;Excuse me?&quot;.<br>
<br>
Another tell, &quot;oh thought u were bot, cast KEI or give plat back plz&quot;.<br>
<br>
A thousand evil things passed through my mind, to do and to say, but I simply handed the 40pp back and walked away. People like that, are why you will NEVER see me selling buffs. And, why I generally ignore shouts and auctions asking for buffs.<br>
